contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|Diablo|diablo}} '''Diablo''' {{IPA-es|di.'a.βlo||}} is a word in Spanish meaning "devil". It may refer to: * [[Devil]], a supernatural entity believed in many religions and cultures to be the personification of evil and the enemy of God and humankind * [[Diablos Motorcycle Club|Diablos MC]], a motorcycle club * [[Lamborghini Diablo]], an Italian sports car * [[Diablo Data Systems]], a division of Xerox ** [[Diablo 630]], a daisy wheel printer * [[USS Diablo (SS-479)|USS ''Diablo'' (SS-479)]], an American submarine * [[Diablo wind]], a type of hot, dry wind * [[Diablo homolog]], a gene * Diablos, name for [[Mission Viejo High School]] sports teams {{TOC right}} == Fiction == * [[Diablo (Marvel Comics)]], a Fantastic Four villain * [[El Diablo (comics)]], a DC Comics hero * [[Diablo (Disney)]], a fictional raven from the 1959 Disney film ''Sleeping Beauty'' * Diablo, a character from ''[[Third and Indiana]]'' == Music == * [[Diablo (band)]], a Finnish metal band * [[Diablo (song)|"Diablo" (song)]], a song by Simon Curtis * "Diablo", a song by [[666 (band)|666]] * "Diablo", a song by Alejandra Guzman from ''[[Soy (Alejandra Guzmán album)|Soy]]'' == Video games == * [[Diablo (series)|''Diablo'' (series)]], a dark fantasy video game series ** [[Diablo (video game)|''Diablo'' (video game)]], the first game of the series ** Diablo, the title [[Characters of Diablo#Diablo|character of the series]] == Places == * [[Diablo, California]], U.S. * [[Mount Diablo]], California, U.S. * [[Diablo Grande AVA]], California wine region in Stanislaus County * [[Diablo, Panama]], a township in the Panama Canal Zone * [[Diablo, Washington]], a community in [[Whatcom County, Washington]], U.S. == See also == * [[El Diablo (disambiguation)]] * [[Diabolo (disambiguation)]] * ''[[Diabolos]]'', an album by Gackt {{disambig|geo}}
